snippet.textDisplay: 4 big guns werent even close to the class of Junaid bhai..thats what makes JJ a legand. Faisal was the most impressive voice out of all. This is the second comment for this video as my heart forces me to protest how lack luster and low effort was put into making this song which was awaited since season 10 was announded. Even if voices didnt suit the original at least some effort could had been made in the music side which too was so basic and turn off to hear in short 'boooring'. Dnt know what will overcome the damage season 10 has given to the coke studio label.  Out of just a very few exceptional songs rest were just to appeal the broad masses which ruins creativity and especiality feel to a song, which was sole reason to rise coke studio to its fame.

snippet.textDisplay:
The covers or remakes I loved from this season:

Episode 1:
Ali Sethi - Ranjish Hi Sahi

Episode 2:
Junoon Ft RFAK, Ali Noor - Sayonee
Kaavish, Quratulain Balouch - Faasle
Ali Zafar - Jaan-e-Bahaaraan 

Episode 3:
Sahir Ali Bagga, Aima Baig - Baazi

Episode 4:
Javed Bashir, Akbar Ali Ft Aamir Zaki - Naina Moray

Episode 5:
Attaullah Esakhelvi, Sanwal Esakhelvi - Sab Maya Hai
RFAK - Rangrez

Episode 6:
Umair Jaswal, Jabar Abbas - Dam Mast Qalandar (This one is less favourite as compared to other ones, just felt that this type of vocal style has been covered so many times, it could've been differently amazing)

Episode 7: 
Sajjad Ali - Tera Naam (Don't know but it does sound like the old Pakistani song Tera Naam Hatheli' to me. However a beautiful song).
Shuja Haider, Aima Baig - Baanware (Mostly because of Shuja Haider's voice chords)
